 stroll to describe my two meetings with your celebrated father. Thefirst was at the opera in the days of the First Duma. I knew, of course, theportraits of its most prominent members. From high up in the gods I, a poorstudent, saw him appear in a rosy loge with his wife and two little boys,one of which must have been you. The other time was at a public discussionof current politics in the auroral period of the Revolution; he spokeimmediately after Kerenski, and the contrast between our fiery fr